<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Brewers Blamed for Using Fertilizers as </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Participants in a
seminar on bad cultures and traditions have called for an end to
the practice of using chemical fertilizers as one of the
addictives in some breweries of Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The practice, which aims at increasing the bitterness of beer,
is dangerous as it will affect a lot of people's health, said a
participant in the one-day seminar in Babati District, "Sunday Times"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
"For sure, fertilizers are poisonous and those who use it in
the brewing should stop forthwith, " she told more than 100
participants from various villages of Babati, Hanang and Mbulu
districts.
</P>
<P>
The participants urged local brewers to stop using fertilizers
and go back to the traditional methods of using cereals only.
</P>
</TEXT>
