<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Holds AIDS Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Ahead of World AIDS
(Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome) Day Monday, Israeli National
AIDS Steering Committee today held a seminar on AIDS at Kfar
Hamaccabiah in northern Israel.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, AIDS experts from all over the country
discussed new AIDS treatments, such as "cocktail," which was
introduced worldwide two years ago and makes AIDS more a chronic
disease than an acute one.
</P>
<P>
The experts also exchanged views on AIDS patients' rights; the
economic and social implications of the disease and the funds
raising for AIDS patients.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest Israeli Health Ministry statistics, a
total of 467 Israelis have contracted full-fledged AIDS since
1981, and 89 of them are still alive and live in Israel.
</P>
<P>
There have also been 1,646 reported HIV carriers in Israel -
1,548 of them alive - but the actual number is estimated to be
twice that or more. The Human Immunedeficiency Virus causes AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 66 AIDS experts from Egypt, Morocco, Jordan, Turkey
and the Palestinian National Authority arrived in Jerusalem Friday
to attend a four-day conference in an attempt to find ways of
reducing the spread of AIDS in the Middle East. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
