<HEADLINE> PNA, German Signed Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 30 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) and Germany signed today in Ramallah a cooperation
agreement under which Germany will finance several development
projects in the PNA territories.
</P>
<P>
PNA Finance Minister Mohammed Zuhdi Nashashebi and visiting
German State Minister of Economy and Development Luther Klem
signed the agreement in the presence of PNA Chairman Yasser
Arafat, according to the Palestinian news service JMCC.
</P>
<P>
German representative to the PNA Horst Fretig, who also
attended the signing ceremony, has called on Israel to implement
the second-stage troop redeployment from the West Bank under
signed agreements.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of opening a safe passage route
linking the West Bank and Gaza Strip, lifting closure Israel
imposed on the PNA territories, and removing Israeli "roadblocks"
to international assistance, economic and infrastructure projects
to the PNA.
</P>
<P>
He called for the implementation of signed agreements
concerning the peace process and the parties concerned not to
take any measure that would have a negative impact on the
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
He said Germany holds that the settlement activities are the
main obstacle to the peace process and which are against the
international law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
