<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Industrial Output Goes up in First Eleven Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's industrial production
in the first eleven months increased by 13.1 percent over the same
period last year, Vietnam's General Department of Statistics said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign enterprises took the lead with the highest growth rate
of 20 percent, followed by state-run enterprises with 11 percent
and the non-state sector with 9.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Production of cement, vegetable oil, medicines in tablets and
detergent saw increases of 25.5 percent, 25.3 percent, 19.3
percent and 23.5 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Output of electricity went up by 12.5 percent, crude oil by
11.8 percent, rolled steel 10.2 percent and garments 13.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Declines, however, were registered in the country's output of
textile, chemical fertilizers, sugar, electric transformers,
electric fans and medicines in ampules. 
</P>
