<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Jo Bonfrere of the Netherlands
and Kalman Mezsoly of Hungary have been short-listed for the
vacant job of the Nigerian national soccer squad.
</P>
<P>
"Our last meeting for the year comes up on December 17. There,
the NFA will pick one of the two men to prepare the team for the
World Cup finals," said Abdulmumini Aminu, chairman of the
Nigerian Football Association (NFA).
</P>
