<HEADLINE> Press Freedom Prevails in HK: Anson Chan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Press freedom, a concern of
people before handover, still prevails in Hong Kong after July 1,
Administrative Secretary Anson Chan told a press seminar here
today.
</P>
<P>
Over 90 media practitioners and academics from China's interior
 areas, Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan were here attending the
professional meeting.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the seminar this evening,
Chan said that there has been no change in the operation of the
local media sector since July 1.
</P>
<P>
She stressed the free flow of information as critical to both
political and economic and trade development of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Without it (free flow of information), Hong Kong's competitive
edge as a cosmopolitan will be diminished and its reputation as a
regional information center damaged, she warned.
</P>
<P>
For that reason, Chan affirmed, protecting and pushing forward
press freedom is a steadfast policy of the Special Administrative
Region government.
</P>
<P>
It is the second time for the seminar to be held in Hong Kong.
The first was held four years ago.
</P>
<P>
Topics to be discussed in the following two days include
balance between press freedom and social responsibilities, media
exchange between the four places in recent years and a review of
media coverage of the handover.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong News Executives' Association played host to the
seminar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
