<HEADLINE> Freestyle Skiing Events Cancelled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Two World Cup freestyle skiing
aerial events were cancelled because of lack of snow, the
International Ski Federation (FIS) said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Warm temperatures have prevented the staging of the season
opener at Tignes, France this weekend, and the aerial competition
in Muju, South Korea in February has been cancelled for economic
reasons.
</P>
<P>
The lack of snow is also threatening other pre-Christmas events
in nearby La Plagne, Kirchberg, Austria and Piancavallo, Italy.
</P>
<P>
However, organisers are still hoping to run mogul competitions
on the glacier at Tignes on Friday and Saturday. 
</P>
