<HEADLINE> Myanmar Reduces Sentences to Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar State Peace and
Development Council (SPDC) issued an order today on reducing the
terms of prisoners who were sentenced before November 15.
</P>
<P>
The move came 15 days after the SPDC was formed on November 15.
</P>
<P>
Radio Myanmar reported tonight that the reduction covers those
prisoners who were sentenced to death, life imprisonment or a term
of more than 10 years.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the order, those given the death penalty are
to be reduced to from life imprisonment to 20 years. Others are to
be cut down to 20 or 15 or 10 years in jail.  
