<HEADLINE> Passenger Train Goes To Scenic Spot In Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- A train on the Nanning-Kunming
railway, which opened to traffic on November 30, carried 600
passengers today to Shilin (Stone Forest), a famous tourist spot
in southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
It is the first train of the 898-kilometer Nanning-Kunming line
to visit the scenic spot in Lunan Autonomous County, where the Yi
ethnic group lives.
</P>
<P>
The train leaves Kunming, the capital of Yunnan, at 07:52 and
arrives at 10:45. A train from Weishe in Guizhou Province takes
visitors back to Kunming at 18:45.
</P>
<P>
The Shilin scenic spot is famous for its stones in various
shapes and special folk arts of local ethnic groups. In recent
years, more than one million people have visited Shilin and other
parts of the county every year.  
</P>
