<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets German Businessmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng said here today
that China would provide preferential tariff terms to the imports
of the technology-advanced equipment which meets the requirement
of China's industry policy.
</P>
<P>
Li made this remark during a meeting with Juergen Schrempp,
chairman of the Board of Daimler-Benz of Germany, and the members
of the company's Board of International Advisers,
</P>
<P>
