<P>
Li noted that China's economy has witnessed great expansion and
a buyer's market has emerged in the country. With the growth of
China's economic and technological strength, he added, the
starting point for Sino-foreign cooperation moves to a higher
level, and China would pay more attention to and encourage
Sino-foreign collaboration in the field of new and high technology.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China hopes that Benz and other foreign
enterprises, while doing trade with China, should cooperate with
the country in such fields as agriculture, basic industries and
information industry, and participate actively in the retooling of
the country's large and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier expressed the hope that Benz, taking the
advantage of its product quality and management, would make new
efforts in the above-mentioned cooperation fields.
</P>
<P>
Schrempp told Li that his company highly appraises the
achievements China has made in its reform and opening-up and is
optimistic about its economic prospect. China is a major
cooperative partner of Benz in Asia and the country bears large
market potential, he said.
</P>
<P>
Daimler-Benz has already set up 15 joint-ventures in China with
an investment of more than 500 million US dollars, Schrempp
said. He predicts that Benz's inventment in the country next year
would surpass one billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
It was learned the Fifth Session of the Board of International
Advisers of Daimler-Benz, which opened here Sunday, was the first
meeting the company had ever held in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
