<DOCNO> XIE19971201.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest Chinese Province Building Railway In Mountainous Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Guizhou Province, in southwest
China, today started work on its first local railway.
</P>
<P>
The 120-kilometer Liupanshui-Baiguo Railway is being provided
with 2.99 billion yuan in financing by the provincial government,
the Ministry of Railways, and the Ministry of the Coal Industry.
</P>
<P>
The railway is designed to link the Nanning-Kunming and
Guiyang-Kunming trunk lines, and its annual transport capacity
will be 18 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The railway will cross many mountains, rivers, and valleys, and
will need 101 bridges and 56 tunnels, which will account for 57.8
percent of the railway's total length.
</P>
<P>
The railway is expected to help people in Guizhou, one of the
country's poorest provinces, get away from poverty, because it
passes by three coal mines, whose reserves are estimated at five
billion tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
