<HEADLINE> Syrian Deputy PM Condemns US Support for Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Deputy Prime Minister and
Defense Minister Mustafa Tlass has blamed the Mideast peace
stalemate on the U.S. bias toward Israel and backed Iran's
military buildup to counter a Turkish-Israeli alliance.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Egypt's Arabic newspaper Al Ahram, which
published today, Tlass said that the conflict between the Arabs
and Israel will continue in the visible future. He accused the
United States of providing political support for Israel and
allowing the peace process to deteriorate.
</P>
<P>
He warned against the perils caused by the policies of Israeli
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, saying that they can catapult
the area into "new de facto realities of more rabid and ferocious
violence."
</P>
<P>
The senior Syrian official lashed out at the United States for
its sustained and constant military support for Israel, saying
that it provides Israel with the most up-to-date arms and weapons.
</P>
<P>
Instead of pressuring Israel to propel the peace process,
Washington is bringing pressures to bear on the Arabs, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Tlass said that Turkey, backed by a military pact
with Israel, is covetous of Iraqi oil by setting up a security
zone in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore it is in the interest of the Arabs that Iran's
military power be developed," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian defense minister spoke of the recent Iranian war
games in the Gulf, saying that they mirror Tehran's desire to
increase its defense capabilities as it is facing "dangerous
challenges from Israel, the United States and Turkey."
</P>
<P>
Concluding his interview with Al Ahram, Tlass underlined the
need to achieve Arab solidarity to fulfill the higher and supreme
interests of the Arab nation and safeguard and maintain its
security and stability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
