<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac to Attend AIDS Conference in Cote d'Ivoire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
will attend the International Conference on AIDS in Africa to be
held in Abidjan, capital of Cote d'Ivoire, on December 7, said a
presidential source.
</P>
<P>
"This will be for him the occasion to express his proximity in
regard to all the victims of the epidemic," Agence France-Presse
(AFP) quoted the source as saying on the 10th World AIDS Day today.
</P>
<P>
Chirac wishes to help make the international community "more
active" in fighting the epidemic which has the full scale of a
tragedy for the African people and the people in developing
countries, said the source.
</P>
<P>
A United Nations report published last week said that 90
percent of the 30 million AIDS victims in the world are living in
developing countries, and 80 percent of them in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Chirac will also express the will not to leave Africa outside
the door of medical progress achieved over the past several years
in treating the AIDS disease, said the source. 
</P>
</TEXT>
