win the award in five seasons.
</P>
<P>
Local media reports said Ikpeba polled a total of 56 points to
beat off Chadian Japhet N'Doram, who is his team fellow in the
French club, Monaco.
</P>
<P>
Another Nigerian player, Taribo West now playing for the
Italian side of Inter Milan, came in the third place.
</P>
<P>
The three other Nigerian players who have won the honour are
Nwankwo Kanu in 1996, Emmanuel Amuneke in 1994 and Rasheed Yekini
in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted CAF sources as saying at the weekend that
Ikpeba was voted for his consistency at both club and national
sides.
</P>
<P>
Ikpeba, 24, featured prominently in the Nigerian national team
Super Eagles that won the Olympic Gold medal in Atlanta, United
States last year. He scored the second goal against Brazil in the
semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
He shot his French side Monaco to the top of the French League
for the first time this season when he scored a double in their
2-0 win over Chateauroui last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview by the BBC in France, Ikpeba reportedly said
that he is now looking forward to wining something with his club,
maybe as the Champion of France winning the European Cup or UEFA.
</P>
<P>
"I'm looking forward to that and (I'm) also looking forward to
Nigeria doing well in the next World Cup finals," he said.
</P>
