<HEADLINE> Ginkgo Industry Develops Rapidly in Guangxi of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region expects to produce 2.7 million
kilograms of ginkgo in 1997 and the ginkgo industry is emerging
as one of the region's major revenue sources.
</P>
<P>
China is the world's only ginkgo exporter. Guangxi's output of
ginkgo accounts for 40 percent of the national total and the region
ranks second only to east China's Jiangsu province in terms of
output.
</P>
<P>
Guilin, the region's major gingko production base, plans to
grow ginkgo on 93,000 hectares by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Plans for the next 10 years call for Guangxi to invest some 230
million yuan (30 million US dollars) to build 13,000 hectares of
gingko plantations and 10 gingko processing plants in 18
poverty-stricken counties.
</P>
<P>
The region's output value of gingko is expected to hit two
billion yuan (250 million US dollars) in 2015, by then the
industry will have helped more than one million farmers escape
poverty.  
</P>
</TEXT>
