<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's human rights
commission today charged that some detainees in connection with
the October 28 coup attempt have been physically tortured by
police authorities, Zambia News Agency ZANA reported.
</P>
<P>
ZANA quoted Jutice Lombe, the human rights watchdog's
chairperson, as saying at a news conference here this morning
that during the commision's tour of prisons where the detainees
are being held, commissioners established that some suspects were
tortured by the police.
</P>
<P>
The commission accordingly condemns the action of the police
officers who engaged themselves in such "sordid" activities, said
the chairperson.
</P>
