action against the officers involved in the tortures and ensure
that the same conduct does not repeat itself.
</P>
<P>
Up till now, at least 84 people who are allegedly involved in
the October military coup have been detained by police under the
country's state of emergency laws.
</P>
<P>
On October 28, a group of dissident army soldiers staged a
military coup to overthrow the Zambian government led by
President Frederick Chiluba. However, the coup was crushed within
several hours. 
