<HEADLINE> China Develops New Anti-Virus Software </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- China has developed new
anti-virus software to protect its fledgling computer industry.
</P>
<P>
The software, known as "Xingtian-98" (Skywalker-98), can detect
and kill more than 11,000 types of viruses, including hidden
viruses on hard disks.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the Beijing Science and Technology Commission
note that the software, developed by a Beijing High-Tech Company,
has reached the world's advanced levels.
</P>
<P>
Computer viruses have surfaced as a major threat to China's
information highway, arousing great concern by the Chinese
government.
</P>
<P>
China's most popular anti-virus software was developed by the
Ministry of Public Security. 
</P>
