<HEADLINE> Shanghai Reports Good Autumn Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai harvested 1.6 million
tons of grain this autumn, a level approaching last year's
record harvest.
</P>
<P>
Reports from local agricultural department indicate that the
city's total grain output this year stood at 2.18 million tons,
including the summer grain output.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai thus fulfilled its goal of producing two million tons
of grain a year.
</P>
<P>
Local agronomists note that the quality of autumn grain
has improved greatly due to the wide use of improved varieties of
rice.
</P>
<P>
However, the good harvest will not lead to a rise in the income
of farmers, because the average autumn grain purchasing price in
the city dropped by 25 percent this year compared to the 1996
level and the cost for agricultural production means rose by three
percent.
</P>
<P>
Supply has now exceeded demand on Shanghai's autumn grain market,
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
