eastern France Sunday banned Le Pen from placing a spray of flower
in the national necropolis of Morette, which commemorates the dead
in the resistance movement against Germany during World War II.
</P>
<P>
-- Demonstrations and other activities will be held today
across France to mark the 10th World AIDS Day organized by the
World Health Organization with the theme of "Children in the World
Targeted by AIDS." The associations engaged in the fight against
AIDS, which are short of money and manpower after the arrival of
tritherapy proved capable of treating AIDS, will remind people
that the fight has not yet ended. Five thousand people are
infected with HIV/AIDS virus each year in France and 30,000 people
in France carry HIV/AIDS virus without knowing it. 
</P>
