<HEADLINE> Trade of Shanghai with Taiwan Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The total import and export
volume of Shanghai, China's largest industrial center, with Taiwan
hit 1.69 billion US dollars in the first three quarters of the
year, up 12.7 percent on the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's exports to Taiwan in the period stood at 364 million
U.S. dollars, up 37.6 percent, and its imports from the latter
were 1.335 billion U.S. dollars, up 7.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises accounted for 1.32 billion
U.S. dollars of the total trade volume, up 14 percent on the same
1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Imports of sythetic fiber, textiles, steel and computer
components, among others, increased while those of machine tools
and textile machinery reduced in the period.
</P>
<P>
In export, inreases were reported in electronic and
machinery products, garments and aquatic products, and reduction
in steel, feather and down.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
