<HEADLINE> China Penalizes Foreigners Working Illegally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-two foreigners who were
found to be working and living illegally in Hangzhou, capital of
east China's Zhejiang Province, were given warnings or various
penalties recently.
</P>
<P>
All of them are urged to go through procedures for living and
employment within fixed term.
</P>
<P>
The action was the result of the city's Public Security and
Labor departments' decisions that followed Chinese Government and
State Council regulations on foreigners working in China.
</P>
<P>
According to the local labor department, there are over 530
overseas people working in the city.
</P>
<P>
The action was also supported by foreign businessmen. One
Japanese investor said, "All countries have their own regulations
on employing foreigners. We should abide by the Chinese laws, so
long as we work in the country."  
</P>
</TEXT>
