<HEADLINE> Nigeria GDP to Rise 3.8 Percent This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria is expected to record a
3.8 percent growth in its gross domestic product (GDP) this year,
according to the Central Bank.
</P>
<P>
The estimated growth rate would be higher than last year's 3.4
percent, Central Bank Governor Paul Ogwuma said over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
However, the level of growth is "considered too low to support
sustained economic growth", the apex bank boss added.
</P>
<P>
According to him, major factors constraining economic
performance include under-capacity operation of the manufacturing
sector, liquidity overhang, huge external debt stock, and low
level of foreignty investment inflow, among others. 
</P>
