<HEADLINE> Folk Art Activities Promoted in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- To attract more tourists and
provide entertainment for local people, the government of Hengshan
County, in central China's Hunan Province, has put 600,000 yuan
annually into traditional art development for past several years,
and a variety of folk art activities have grown up.
</P>
<P>
The culture department has set up more than 150 art troupes
consisting of 2,600 folk artists for leather-silhouette shows,
flower-drum opera performances, song and dance performances, and
dragon-dance shows.
</P>
<P>
The artists have developed 140 new song programs and 23 have
won national prizes. They have also developed a number of modern
operas with patriotic themes that were well received by a large
number of local audience. More than 300,000 people have watched
the performances.
</P>
<P>
The county has also set up many culture palaces and recreation
centers where people can enjoy many activities. 
