<HEADLINE> Shanghai Consumer Market Shows Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The consumer market in
Shanghai has shown stable growth and is expected to exceed 134
billion yuan (17 billion U.S. dollars) in retail sales volume this
year.
</P>
<P>
Local statistics show that the city had a retail sales volume
of 108.85 billion yuan (12.6 billion US dollars) in the first 10
months of this year, 15.2 percent more than the same period last
year. Shanghai ranked first in retail sales volume among the
country's 25 major commercial cities.
</P>
<P>
Monthly retail sales exceeded 10 billion yuan (1.25 billion
U.S. dollars), according to statistics.
</P>
<P>
The consumer price index and the retail price index stood at
102.9 percent and 99.1 percent, respectively, for the
January-October period.
</P>
<P>
During that period, Shanghai's gross domestic product (GDP) was
270.432 billion yuan, including 30.662 billion yuan from
commercial business.
</P>
<P>
The number of chain stores topped 880 and produced six billion
yuan (750 million U.S. dollars) in retail sales for the first 10
months, according to statistics. 
</P>
