<HEADLINE> Tianjin Increases Investments in Foreign Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, the largest port city
in northern China, has opened 176 enterprises and offices in 23
countries.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin, a municipality directly administered by the central
government, has also established friendly city ties with 43 cities
in 32 countries.
</P>
<P>
"Friendly city ties serve as a bridge for promoting bilateral
economic and trade cooperation," according to Zhao Jianzhong, a
section chief with the Tianjin Municipal Commission for Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
One Tianjin timber plant has taken advantage of friendly ties
to invest 4.5 million US dollars in Brazil, with a Tianjin tractor
plant investing 2.45 million US dollars in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
