<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas-Funded Businesses Doing Well in Central Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to an improved investment
climate, overseas-funded businesses in the capital of east China's
Anhui Province are doing well.
</P>
<P>
The city of Hefei had 1,151 overseas-funded enterprises by
September this year, with 4.2 billion US dollars in total
investment, which have contributed a great deal to the local
economy.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of the year, overseas-funded enterprises had
4.2 billion yuan in output, nearly 3.6 billion yuan in sales, 280
million yuan in pre-tax profits, and nearly 22 million US dollars
in foreign exchange from exports. All these figures were up by a
large margin from the same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of big-name companies like the U.S.'s Coca
Cola, Japan's Hitachi and Sanyo, and Switzerland's ABB, have
invested in Hefei.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded enterprises have also purchased or merged with
some local state-owned companies that were on the edge of
bankruptcy. In past two years, a number of local money-losing
state enterprises, with 1.2 billion yuan of assets, have gotten a
new lease on life by these means, and a large number of laid-off
workers have found new jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
