<DOCNO> XIE19971201.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Ministers Agree on Surveillance Mechanism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 1 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN finance ministers
have agreed to form a regional surveillance mechanism within ASEAN
as a preventive effort to avoid the emergence of risk that would
precipitate a crisis.
</P>
<P>
The ministers said in their joint statement at the end of the
special meeting here today that the criteria for surveillance
would be developed by the ASEAN Central Bank Forum formed on
November 5 this year.
</P>
<P>
To set the criteria for surveillance, the forum with the
objective of evaluating potential economic and financial risks of
member countries, highlighting policy options and implications and
encouraging early action to minimize such risks, would consult the
relevant international financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN Select Committee comprising members of the ASEAN
Central Bank Forum and financial officials would form the core of
the mutual surveillance process.
</P>
<P>
The ministers agreed that the ASEAN finance ministers process
would be supported by its own permanent secretariat in order to
facilitate this initiative.
</P>
<P>
The ministers also welcomed the proposal by the Philippines to
seek the assistance of the Asian Development Bank to develop an
initial framework for the establishment of the secretariat and its
terms of reference.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint press conference, the meeting's chairman
and Thai Finance Minister Tarrin Nimmanhaeminda said ASEAN would
approach the ADB in the hope that the latter would take up the
matter.
</P>
<P>
Apart from getting the surveillance criteria, the secretariat
would have the task of developing the basic data among member
countries which would be used as a framework for reference and
discussion, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
