<HEADLINE> Chinese City Sets Up Arbitration Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 1 (Xinhua) -- A foreign affairs arbitration
office has opened in Wuhan, capital of central China's
Hubei province.
</P>
<P>
The office will offer legal mediation and arbitration services
to foreign-funded enterprises and institutes as well as
foreign entrepreneurs in the city.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan has witnessed an increasing number of economic disputes
in recent months. The office will mediate disputes and help
related parties reach satisfactory agreements.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan has established economic and trade relations with more
than 100 countries and regions, and currently exports nearly 1,000
commodities to other countries.
</P>
<P>
The office will also help improve the city's investment
environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
