<DOCNO> XIE19971201.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea, IMF Reach Agreement on Terms of Bailout Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 1 (Xinhua) -- South Korea and the International
Monetary Fund (IMF) reached an agreement early today on the terms
of an IMF rescue package, a spokesman of the Ministry of Finance
and Economy said.
</P>
<P>
"The government will announce the agreement after its approval
at an extraordinary cabinet meeting scheduled for today," the
spokesman told Xinhua, adding that the IMF will soon hold a
special board meeting to approve the agreement.
</P>
<P>
The details of the agreement was not available at this time.
</P>
<P>
Yonhap News Agency said the IMF fund is expected to amount to
50 to 60 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is the third recipient in Asia of IMF funds after
Thailand and Indonesia since August following a wave of steep
currency depreciations caused by massive debt overhangs in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank and the Asian Development Bank (ADB) have said
they will contribute to the South Korea's efforts to tide over the
crisis and Japan has also indicated it will give some support.
</P>
<P>
Hit hard by a great number of corporate bankruptcies and
defaults, several South Korean commercial and merchant banks are
on the brink of collapse. Markets in the country have been in
turmoil and stock prices have plunged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
