<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Candidates for HKSAR Deputies to China's National </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Presidium of the
Conference for Electing Deputies of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) to the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC) of China made public the list of candidates here
today.
</P>
<P>
The 72 candidates each obtained nomination by at least 10
members of the 424-strong Election Conference from November 13 to
28.
</P>
<P>
According to the Election Method, as the number of nominees
exceeds the number to be elected (36) by more than one-half, a
preliminary election will be held on the morning of December 6 to
determine the 54 official candidates on the merit of votes. The
final election is scheduled for December 8.
</P>
<P>
The Presidium of the Election Conference held a meeting here
this morning to review the nomination process which was "open,
fair and just."
</P>
<P>
An announcement made by the Presidium this afternoon said that
during the nomination period of November 13 to 28, a total of 139
people came to get Registration Forms and 74 of them handed in the
 Registration Forms together with Nomination Letters. Only 72
become candidates as they obtained enough Nomination Letters with
the other two failing to obtain 10 Nomination Letters.  
</P>
