<HEADLINE> Thai Paddy Output to Hit 17.83m Tons Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's main-season paddy
output is expected to reach 17.83 million tons next year, up 0.32
percent from this year despite the anticipated drought and
dwindling growing areas.
</P>
<P>
The forecast paddy output rise is based on a recent survey by
the Thai Agriculture and Cooperatives Ministry which was published
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Thai rice farmers are planning to use new planting methods to
increase their yields to meet the higher demand for Thai rice on
the market next year, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The Thai rice export volume is also expected to hit 5.3 million
tons worth 53 billion baht (1.32 billion U.S. dollars), as Thai
farmers will enjoy good prices on the world market next year, the
ministry said.
</P>
<P>
However, the ministry said, the total growing areas across
Thailand will be at 57.17 million lai (9.14 million hectares) next
year, down 0.21 percent from this year.  
</P>
