succeeded in making profits after paying off all debts will
receive front-page coverage of the country's leading newspaper
from today on.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Anda Cotton Textile Plant is expected to make up all
losses by the end of this year since it has successfully decreased
losses to 187,000 yuan from 30 million yuan over the period of
Jan-Oct.
</P>
<P>
Anda was a newborn based on a big losing textile factory and
the only profit-making textile factory in Shanghai in June,
1996. Anda cut down the number of workforce by 40 percent and
reduced 36,000 spindles. By optimizing assets, Anda achieved
obvious economic returns.
</P>
<P>
-- The key lies on confidence, said People's Daily's front-page
commentary hailing Anda's practice. It believed that the 10
enterprises will give good examples of how to push forward reform
on state-owned enterprises and extricate them from difficult
positions.
