<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction of comfort Housing to be Curbed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Comfort housing scheme, a
nationwide program to provide basic housing for those with less
per capita living space, may be restricted as more vacant space
has emerged since the project's implementation in 1995.
</P>
<P>
By the first half of this year, completed floor space had
reached 5.03 million sq. m, according to statistics from the
Ministry of Construction.
</P>
<P>
However, some 3.39 million sq. m. of the cheapest Comfort
housing remain vacant in June this year, accounting for 66 percent
of completed space, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Shen Jianzhong, deputy director of the real estate department
of the Ministry of Construction said problems centered on lack of
affordability and poor quality projects.
</P>
<P>
Although the price of Comfort housing is limited to 1,000 yuan
per sq. m., only about four percent of China's urban households
earn more than 5,000 yuan a year. It will take more than 10 years
for those benefiting under the Comfort scheme to buy a home with a
floor space of 55 sq. m., he added.
</P>
<P>
Comfort housing should be limited to a suitable scale when the
residential housing reform is intensified, Shen said.
</P>
<P>
Given favourable policies and lower prices, Comfort houses
would have been sold out, said an expert.
</P>
<P>
Comfort housing scheme benefits from a series of preferential
policies in terms of bank loans and land use, It has been
introduced in 232 cities with a total designated floor space of
42.15 million sq. m. Buyers of Comfort housing must be below a
certain level of household income, which differs according to the
local government areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
