<HEADLINE> HK NPC Deputies Election Conference Presidium Meets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Presidium of the
Conference for Electing Deputies of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) to the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC) of China is meeting here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Chaired by Tung Chee Hwa, executive chairman of the Presidium,
the 11 Presidium members are expected to review the 72 nominees to
run for the 36 NPC deputies and discuss a proposed list of
scrutineers and other matters related to the election.
</P>
<P>
A list of candidates for the NPC deputies is expected to be
made public after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
By November 28, the deadline set for the nomination of HKSAR
deputies to Ninth NPC, 72 people had been nominated for the
election of the 36 deputies. They had each obtained nomination by
at least 10 members of the 424-strong Election Conference.
</P>
<P>
According to the Election Method, as the number of nominees
exceeds the number to be elected by more than one-half, a
preliminary round of election will take place on December 6 to
decide the 54 official candidates. The final election is scheduled
for December 8.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for Hong Kong to elect deputies to the
NPC as an independent constituency since China resumed the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1 this year.
</P>
