<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy to Repatriate Illegal Albanian Immigrants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Italy will start repatriating
illegal Albanian immigrants Monday in accordance with a directive
signed by Italian Prime Minister Romao Prodi.
</P>
<P>
The premier said when signing the directive that the
repatriation operation would not be postponed.
</P>
<P>
Hours before the repatriation was to begin, tension was running
high among 524 illegal Albanians in Puglia because they were
unclear how the operation was to be carried out and how long it
would take.
</P>
<P>
Many said that they had the necessary requisites to obtain a
sojourn permit, either because they were to join family members in
Italy, or because they had work contracts, or because they needed
medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
A young woman, speaking for around 150 Albanians at Cassano
Murge, near Bari, announced that they would stage a hunger strike.
</P>
<P>
Waves of Albanians began to flood the coasts of Puglia in
March. Many have since left but 4,789 Albanians without proper
documents still remain in Italy, according to the Interior
Ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
