<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, December 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif said Monday
the country's constitutional crisis was created out of petty
issues and vowed "to rid the country of corruption, terrorism and
lawlessness."
</P>
<P>
In a nationwide TV and Radio broadcast here Monday evening,
Sharif, in power for nine months, said that "a stable government
has been plunged into an atmosphere of uncertainty owing to the
wishes of a few people." (BC-Pakistan-PM-Address)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- British government is calling for tighter transplant
checks after tissue from the eyes of a woman with CJD, or human
equivalency of mad cow disease, was transplanted into three other
people.
</P>
<P>
Marion Hamilton, 53, who died of lung cancer, was later found
to have CJD, the BBC television reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The information was reportedly not passed on to doctors
supervising the transplants.
</P>
<P>
The fatal disease may be infected by contacting any tissue from
the patient. (BC-UK-Mad Cow Disease)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Cabinet decided Monday to defer the second
troop redeployment in the West Bank until a ministerial committee
formulates a final map on Israeli interests and the Palestinian
side fulfills its peace commitments.
</P>
<P>
A government statement issued after the weekly Cabinet meeting
said the cabinet, in a vote of 16 in favor and two abstentions,
decided in principle to carry out further redeployment.
</P>
<P>
But the extent and timetable for the second redeployment will
only be decided by a ministerial committee headed by Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. (BC-Israel-Redeployment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- The new output ceiling set by the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) will depress crude oil prices
on the international market to less than 18 U.S. dollars a barrel
in 1998, experts here said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ali Akber, marketing manager of the Abu Dhabi National Oil
Company (ADNOC), said that the output increase will deal a severe
blow to oil prices, which fluctuate around 18.5 dollars this
year. (BC-OPEC-Oil Prices)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin and German Chancellor
Helmut Kohl Monday had a 90-minute informal talks at the
presidential residence Rus outside Moscow, the Interfax news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral relations Yeltsin and Kohl agreed to hold annual
top-level meetings with key ministers taking part.
</P>
<P>
They considered the ways of setting up three-sided
consultations involving Russia, France and Germany in line with
the wish expressed by French President Jaques Chirac at the EC
summit in Strasbourg, which is planned to be held in
Yekaterinburg, Russia, in the first half of
1998. (BC-Russia-Germany-Visit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
