<HEADLINE> United States, China To Host World Basketball Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Indianapolis of the United States
would hold the 2002 men's world championships with China hosting
the women's event, announced the executive committee of FIBA,
basketball's ruling body here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Indianapolis beat out the other two finalists Tokyo and Munich
after they made their last bids on Sunday in Munich before the
15-member FIBA.
</P>
<P>
The men's championship is scheduled in the first two weeks of
September while the women's tournament will run from May 26 to
June 6 in the town of Suzhou and Changzhou of Jiangshu province
with the final in Nanjing
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time for the United States to host the
event.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 world championship is scheduled for Athens of Greece.
</P>
<P>
FIBA also set the dates for the basketball tournament at the
2000 Olympics in Sydney from September 16 to October 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
