<DOCNO> XIE19971201.0234 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Promises Cooperation with Spain Against ETA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 30 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin today promised to discuss profoundly with Spanish leaders
bilateral cooperation to fight the terrorism perpetuated by the
Basque separatist group ETA.
</P>
<P>
Jospin made the statement to the Spanish newspaper El Periodico
de Catalunya on the eve of the Franco-Spanish summit to be held on
Monday and Tuesday in the Spanish city of Salamanque.
</P>
<P>
The summit, the 11th between France and Spain, will be focused
on European construction and anti-terrorist cooperations.
</P>
<P>
The French Interior Minister Jean-Pierre Chevenement also said
in an interview with the Spanish daily ABC that ETA can no longer
consider France as a refuge or sanctuary.
</P>
<P>
He said that 140 ETA activists were arrested in France in 1996
and 53 arrested in the first half of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The last time France granted the status of political refugee to
ETA members was in 1986 and there is now only one ETA member who
lives legally as a political refugee in France, said Chevenement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
